00:04:24.550 --> 00:04:25.300
list of them.

00:04:25.300 --> 00:04:27.630
So let's talk about
all the fractions.

00:04:27.630 --> 00:04:30.640
Let's call it F, all the
fractions between 0 and 12.

00:04:30.640 --> 00:04:34.680
So 1/2 will be in there.

00:04:34.680 --> 00:04:36.530
2/3 will be in there.

00:04:36.530 --> 00:04:38.540
4/3 will be in there,
whatever.

00:04:38.540 --> 00:04:40.750
If that's listable,
let's measure the

00:04:40.750 --> 00:04:42.570
length of all of them.

00:04:42.570 --> 00:04:44.860
So the length, what's
the length of 1/2?

00:04:44.860 --> 00:04:45.660
Well, that's 0.

00:04:45.660 --> 00:04:46.790
What's the length of 2/3?

00:04:46.790 --> 00:04:47.610
Well, that's 0.

00:04:47.610 --> 00:04:48.510
What's the length of 4/3?

00:04:48.510 --> 00:04:49.310
Well, that's 0.

00:04:49.310 --> 00:04:51.680
Boo, boo, boo, boo, boo, boo.

